main event: A civilian observed three hovering objects in Pueblo, Colorado on 11 August 1965.
interesting points: The objects were described as round, with one larger object emitting red, green, and white lights., The observation lasted approximately 20 minutes, and the objects appeared to be stationary at times., The conclusion suggested that the sighting likely corresponded to known astronomical phenomena, particularly a bright star., The witness's reliability was noted as fair, raising questions about the accuracy of the report., The sighting was investigated by Air Force officials who found no conclusive evidence supporting the presence of physical objects.
sighted object: one large and two smaller round objects
